cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV. 

This paper is about designing a walking pattern generator for a biped robot, which involves optimization and control techniques. The paper focuses on generating robust gaits that can prevent the robot from falling down in the presence of severe disturbances. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), which deals with the design, construction, operation, and use of robots. 

The paper also uses optimization techniques such as Quadratic Programming (QP) to decide the next step location and timing, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. 

Moreover, the paper uses machine learning techniques to generate walking patterns, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. 

The paper also uses simulation results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper uses computer vision techniques to measure the Divergent Component of Motion (DCM), which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category.
